</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm217260912">
<problem id="fs-idm128376592">
<para id="fs-idm206945136">Explain why sulfuric acid, H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>, which is a covalent molecule, dissolves in water and produces a solution that contains ions.</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm172430496">
<problem id="fs-idm98785952">
<para id="fs-idm163724208">How many grams of Epsom salts (MgSO<sub>4</sub>⋅7H<sub>2</sub>O) will form from 5.0 kg of magnesium?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm213278688">
<para id="fs-idm43029600">5.1 <m:math><m:mo>×</m:mo></m:math> 10<sup>4</sup> g</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
